item.title: The Men Who Would Kill the Medici, Part 1
item.description:
Lorenzo de Medici was the center of power in Florence. Three men—Girolomo Riario, Francesco de Pazzi, and Francesco Salviati, Archbishop of Pisa—were determined to take him down. They just needed the authority of a Pope behind them.

item.title: Ep. 101 ~ Meilin Ehlke - Wild Rambling Rose
item.description: Host Meilin Ehlke encourages listeners to connect to oneness and embrace their magnificence, just like the magnificent rambling rose in her garden. This beautiful flower knows when to bloom and show its beauty to the world, just like how we can learn to connect to oneness and showcase our own magnificence.
